Hi David,

The equation of the circle with center (h,k) and radius r is 

  (x - h)^2 + (y - k)^2 = r^2

There are three parameters here (h, k, and r), so three points will
uniquely determine a particular circle:

  http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/55233.html

Does this help? 

- Doctor Ian, The Math Forum
